<title>CANADA: Southam says gets C$86 mln for unit.</title>
<headline>Southam says gets C$86 mln for unit.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1996-09-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Southam Inc said on Monday it closed the sale of its Construction Data Group to a management team and its financial partner, Boston Ventures, for C$86 million or US$63 million.</p>
<p>The sale includes R.S. Means, Construction Market Data, Chapin Publishing, Architects' First Source, Journal of Commerce, Daily Commercial News, Southam Building Reports and Buildcore.</p>
<p>Southam will use the proceeds to reduce short-term debt incurred in buying seven papers from Thomson Corp earlier this month as well as for general corporate purposes.</p>
<p>-- Reuters Toronto Bureau (416) 941-8100</p>
